a pre-tax profit of $20 billion tomorrow, the largest by a
British bank since the financial crisis, the London-based Sunday
Times  reported , without saying where it got the information.  HSBC is also set to reveal the total pay of as many as 300
of its senior employees, pre-empting new rules, the newspaper
reported. Chief Executive Officer Stuart Gulliverâ€™s bonus may be
